{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b2134584-0aa7-4cee-b27e-4f7987a4c2ba","content":"## What happened\n\n.NET has been progressively removing built-in DSA support. On macOS, .NET delegates to Apple's native crypto frameworks (Security.framework), and **Apple no longer supports the DSA algorithm** in those frameworks. Starting with .NET 11, `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS instead of providing a fallback.\n\nOn Windows (CNG) and Linux (OpenSSL), DSA is still available in the platform crypto libraries, so those targets continue to work—for now. DSA is marked obsolete everywhere (`SYSLIB0030`).\n\n## How to fix it\n\n**Option 1 – Use BouncyCastle (recommended if you must keep verifying DSA signatures):**\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\n// Import the legacy DSA public key (e.g. from X.509 SubjectPublicKeyInfo)\nvar pubKey = PublicKeyFactory.CreateKey(spkiBytes);\n\n// Verify signature\nvar verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA1withDSA\"); // or SHA256withDSA\nverifier.Init(forSigning: false, pubKey);\nverifier.BlockUpdate(data, 0, data.Length);\nbool valid = verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n```\n\nBouncyCastle is a fully managed implementation—no platform dependency.\n\n**Option 2 – Migrate to a modern algorithm:**\n\nIf you control both signing and verification, re-sign with **ECDSA** or **Ed25519** (`ECDsa.Create()` / `Ed25519` in .NET 11) and retire DSA entirely. This is the long-term answer since DSA (`SYSLIB0030`) is obsolete on all platforms.\n\n**Option 3 – Platform-conditional code (stop-gap):**\n\n```csharp\nif (OperatingSystem.IsMacOS())\n    return VerifyWithBouncyCastle(data, sig, pubKey);\nelse\n    return VerifyWithBuiltInDsa(data, sig, pubKey);\n```\n\n### TL;DR\n\nApple dropped DSA → .NET 11 on macOS can't call it → use **BouncyCastle** for a managed DSA verifier, and plan to migrate off DSA entirely.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3fdbcb9a-1fe2-4e0f-88b8-d4d7d45c0e11","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS when upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me think about what I know about this topic.\n\nThis is a known breaking change in .NET. Starting with .NET 7, Microsoft began deprecating older cryptographic algorithms, and DSA specifically has been affected on macOS.\n\nThe key issue: Apple's Security framework (and specifically the CommonCrypto/CryptoKit libraries) dropped support for DSA. Since .NET on macOS uses the platform's native crypto libraries, when Apple removed DSA support, .NET on macOS could no longer create DSA instances.\n\n\nOn macOS, calling `DSA.Create()` throws a `PlatformNotSupportedException` because Apple's frameworks no longer support DSA—this was documented as a breaking change starting in .NET 7. Given the timeline where .NET 10 released in November 2025 and .NET 11 would follow in November 2026, this incompatibility would still be present. In .NET 7, DSA-related types were marked obsolete with compiler warnings, and the actual removal or platform-specific blocking came later. For a .NET 10 to .NET 11 transition, the breaking change would likely be the complete removal of DSA support on macOS, where `System.Security.Cryptography.DSA` operations would throw `PlatformNotSupportedException`. Apple's cryptographic frameworks don't support DSA, and .NET no longer provides a managed fallback. To work around this, I could recommend using BouncyCastle for a managed DSA implementation, migrating to ECDSA or Ed25519 if possible, or using a conditional approach that falls back to BouncyCastle on macOS while using the built-in implementation elsewhere.\n\nI should be precise about the version history here—the exact breaking change matters. DSA was marked obsolete in .NET with SYSLIB0030, and eventually started throwing PlatformNotSupportedException on macOS, which aligns with what the user is experiencing between .NET 10 and 11.","outputTokens":1827,"requestId":"6C34:1FF93E:E13183:108A423:69FE92B5"},"id":"5a25a01d-385a-4172-a5ca-04c1519c2a48","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:50:18.908Z","parentId":"cc53d3f7-7df2-4621-ae28-6451cff5e167"}
